					></a
				>
			</div>
		</section>

		<div class="pt-32">
			<ProjectSection
				id="tfc"
				companyColor="#113BB8"
				companyName="Transport for Cairo"
				title="is a boutique consultancy keeping the next 100 mega-cities moving."
				role="I led RouteLab's product design & development."
			>
				<Image
					loading="eager"
					src={TfCLogo}
					alt="Transport for Cairo logo"
					class="aspect-square w-12 rounded-lg bg-white p-2 shadow-lg"
					slot="logo"
				/>

				<Fragment slot="description">
					<p class="pb-8 text-base leading-relaxed">
						I joined the team in November 2019, fresh out of college, to help
						tackle a pressing challenge: the lack of high-quality data hindering
						the development of infrastructure projects in emerging economies.
						TfC's mission is to bring a data-driven approach to the development
						of informal transit systems across Africa. I was part of a team that
						developed a unique set of tools to collect, visualize, and process
						geographical data; battle-tested in some of Africa's densest urban
						environments.
						<br />
						<br />
						As a key member of the team, I focused on UX design and frontend development,
						driving the creation of four geospatial applications under the unified
						RouteLab Design System. One of my notable projects was developing a vehicle
						detection and tracking system, which involved collecting and cleaning
						a large vehicle dataset, training a custom image classifier, and deploying
						it to a scalable micro-service architecture. I also accelerated the data
						validation process by 40% with a web-based geoprocessing tool, leveraging
						GPU power to process hundreds of thousands of geographic data points
						simultaneously. Along the way we created many data-rich interactive dashboards
						to enhance the project monitoring process for data collection projects.

						<br />
						<br />
						The impact of our work was significant. RouteLab improved data accuracy,
						speed, and quality, reducing traditional data collection costs by 75%.
						This made it the go-to tool for large-scale data collection efforts by
						major organizations like the World Bank, AFD, GIZ, and the World Resources
						Institute. I'm proud to have played a key role in shaping the product
						and driving its success.
					</p>

					<Testimonial
						cite="https://www.linkedin.com/in/bishoymaher/"
						avatarSrc={HazemFahmi}
						name="Hazem Fahmi"
						role="Data Analyst"
						content="Bishoy combines solid technical knowledge, an eye for good design, and a remarkable organizational capacity. Working alongside him and under his leadership on multiple projects, I've seen him exercise these qualities on technical and non-technical fronts, guiding and supporting the team, while staying focused and goal-driven. On many occasions, I've seen him very skillfully manage and align the visions of different stakeholders, always prioritizing clear communication, promptly identifying and clearing any ambiguities. Bishoy's skill and vision are valuable to any team he works with. Moreover, he is humble and supportive, and constantly sharing his learnings."
					/>
				</Fragment>

				<ProjectImage
					slot="client-work"
					sx="aspect-[9/19.2]"
					src={IdentificationHome}
					alt="Observer mobile app conducting an identification survey"
				/>

				<ProjectImage
					slot="client-work"
					sx="aspect-[15.3/10]"
					src={ObserverDashboard}
					alt="Observer web dashboard"
				/>
				<ProjectImage
					slot="client-work"
					sx="aspect-[9/17.8]"
					src={OnboardMobileTrack}
					alt="Observer mobile app conducting an onboard survey"
				/>

				<ProjectImage
					slot="client-work"
					sx="aspect-[20/9]"
					src={OnboardDashboard}
					alt="Observer onboard survey web dashboard"
				/>

				<ProjectImage
					slot="client-work"
					sx="aspect-[9/17.8]"
					src={MobileFreqSurvey}
					alt="Observer mobile app conducting a frequency survey"
				/>

				<ProjectImage
					slot="client-work"
					sx="aspect-[5.2/3]"
					src={SnapperH3}
					alt="Observer Onboard Survey Web Dashboard"
				/>
				<ProjectImage
					slot="client-work"
					sx="aspect-[19.3/9]"
					src={SnapperMatchLine}
					alt="Snapper Web GIS Editor"
				/>
				<ProjectImage
					slot="client-work"
					sx="aspect-[4.2/3]"
					src={LensDetector}
					alt="Custom trained YOLOv3 model detecting microbuses, motorcycles, and trucks"
				/>
			</ProjectSection>
		</div>
		<div class="pt-32">
			<ProjectSection
				companyName="Flowly"
				companyColor="#8CBBF2"
				id="flowly"
				title="is a virtual clinic helping patients manage chronic pain & anxiety from the comfort of their home."
				role="We partnered to deliver a seamless experience for our healthcare providers."
			>
				<Image
					loading="lazy"
					src={FlowlyLogo}
					alt="Flowly logo"
					class="aspect-square w-12 rounded-lg bg-white p-2 shadow-lg"
					slot="logo"
				/>

				<Fragment slot="description">
					<p class="pb-8 text-base leading-relaxed">
						I initially joined the team in October of 2021 as a frontend
						engineer to overhaul the product checkout process and build a
						customer experience portal, used internally at Flowly, to better
						support their users. Since then my responsibilities expanded to
						include a full range of both backend and frontend tasks. We
						implemented integrations with Stripe, Shipstation, and Twilio to
						provide various customer support functions.
						<br />
						<br />
						Notable accomplishments include upgrading AWS Amplify and nearly 100
						Lambda functions to meet SOC 2 requirements to acquire SOC 2 Type 1 certification;
						reducing helpdesk response times by 50% with a two-way SMS chat module;
						and contributing to a 10% increase in customer acquisition through multiple
						secondary checkout flows for gifting, tiered users, and enterprise customers.
					</p>
					<Testimonial
						cite="https://www.linkedin.com/in/bishoymaher/"
						avatarSrc={JulienSoros}
						name="Julien Soros"
						role="CTO & Co-founder"
						content="Bishoy is one of the best developers I've worked with. He's extremely organized and diligent which makes meetings and communication super efficient. For our company, he started off working on a frontend react portal but his role quickly grew to encompass a wide range of backend work as well. He's a quick learner and doesn't just complete the work assigned to him but actively thinks about how to improve things. He interfaced well with other team members and stakeholders and was a great team member. I can't recommend him highly enough."
					/>
				</Fragment>

				<ProjectImage
					slot="client-work"
					sx="aspect-[16/10]"
					src={EventsList}
					alt="Flowly portal, managing events"
				/>

				<ProjectImage
					slot="client-work"
					sx="aspect-[17/10]"
					src={UserHomeFlowScore}
					alt="Flowly portal, user homepage"
				/>
			</ProjectSection>
		</div>
		<div class="pt-32">
			<ProjectSection
				companyName="Dexi"
				companyColor="#4498F9"
				id="dexi"
				title="is building the OS for dental clinics."
				role="I led the UX planning & design, and mentored the frontend team."
			>
				<Image
					loading="lazy"
					src={DexiLogo}
					alt="Dexi logo"
					class="aspect-square w-12 rounded-lg bg-white p-2 shadow-lg"
					slot="logo"
				/>
				<Fragment slot="description">
					<p class="pb-8 text-base leading-relaxed">
						The journey began in June 2020, when my brother-in-law, a dentist,
						struggled to find a practice management solution that met his needs.
						He decided to build the solution himself, and I joined him on this
						mission. Over 15 months, we transformed his idea into a reality,
						launching our beta in August 2021.
						<br />
						<br />
						My focus was on crafting a user-centered journey that streamlined different
						workflows based the user's role. I championed an innovative approach
						that separated tasks, allowing doctors to focus on patient care while
						administrative staff handled logistics.
					</p>
					<Testimonial
						cite="https://www.linkedin.com/in/bishoymaher/"
						avatarSrc={EhabGeorge}
						name="Ehab George"
						role="CEO & Co-founder"
						content="Bishoy was a real blessing to our team. His natural sense for the business needs, and ability to translate that to a design vision, allowed us to develop a user flow that was truly disruptive."
					/>
				</Fragment>

				<ProjectImage
					slot="client-work"
					sx="aspect-[9/18.5]"
					src={DashboardMobile}
					alt="Mobile responsive view of the Dexi dashboard"
				/>

				<ProjectImage
					slot="client-work"
					sx="aspect-[16/10.4]"
					src={TreatmentPlanning}
					alt="Treatment planner"
				/>
				<ProjectImage
					slot="client-work"
					sx="aspect-[16/10.4]"
					src={PatientScheduling}
					alt="Patient scheduler"
				/>
				<ProjectImage
					slot="client-work"
					sx="aspect-[16.2/10]"
					src={DashboardDesktop}
					alt="Desktop view of the Dexi dashboard"
				/>
			</ProjectSection>
		</div>

		<section
			class="mx-auto flex w-full max-w-screen-sm flex-col gap-8 border-solid px-8 py-32 text-lg md:px-0"
		>
			<h2
				class="font-serif text-5xl leading-tight tracking-tighter md:text-center md:text-7xl md:leading-none"
			>
				Let&apos;s build a better future, <span
					class="font-serif italic text-sky-600">together</span
				>
			</h2>
			<p class="md:px-12">
				I am currently available for hire as an independent contractor.
				<br />
				<br />
				I can only take on a limited number of projects each year. For this reason,
				I choose to work exclusively with companies that fight climate change, support
				health and wellness, or improve access to education.
				<br />
				<br />
				If that sounds like you, let&apos;s talk!
			</p>

			<div class="flex flex-col gap-3 align-middle md:flex-row md:px-12">
				<button
					class="inline-flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap rounded-3xl bg-primary px-14 py-6 text-lg font-medium text-primary-foreground shadow-md ring-offset-background transition duration-200 ease-in-out hover:-translate-y-1 hover:bg-primary/90 hover:shadow-lg focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:opacity-50"
				>
